    Copyright (C) System76
    Licensed under the GNU General Public License, version 3 or later.

This derivation is part of why the desktop application is licensed under
AGPL-3.0-or-later (see "Why AGPL" above for the other part — the mupdf
dependency).


Dependency license audit
-------------------------

Audited with `cargo deny check licenses` (config: deny.toml) for the Rust
workspace, and a package.json-metadata scan for pwa/'s npm dependencies.
Re-run `cargo deny check licenses` from the repo root to reproduce.

npm (pwa/): every dependency resolves to a permissive license (MIT, ISC,
Apache-2.0, BSD-2/3-Clause, BlueOak-1.0.0, MPL-2.0, CC0-1.0, CC-BY-3.0/4.0,
or a permissive OR-choice). No copyleft, nothing unlicensed.

Rust workspace: the large majority of third-party crates are permissive
(MIT/Apache-2.0/BSD/ISC/Zlib/Unicode-3.0/MPL-2.0/CC0-1.0/Unlicense), plus
one data license (CDLA-Permissive-2.0, covering the bundled Mozilla root
certificate list in `webpki-root-certs` — not source code, no copyleft
obligations). Copyleft dependencies present, all intentional and all
flowing only into the AGPL-3.0-or-later `read-flow`/`read-flow-widgets`/
`read-flow-core` targets:
  - `mupdf` / `mupdf-sys` (Artifex) — AGPL-3.0-only. See "Why AGPL" above.
  - `cosmic-protocols` / `cosmic-client-toolkit` (pop-os) — GPL-3.0-only,
    Wayland protocol bindings pulled in transitively via libcosmic.
    Compatible with AGPL-3.0 (GPLv3 §13 permits combining with AGPLv3).
  - A handful of libcosmic/window_clipboard sub-crates (`cosmic-config`,
    `cosmic-config-derive`, `cosmic-settings-daemon`, `cosmic-theme`,
    `iced_accessibility`, `dnd`, `mime`) omit a `license` field in their
    own Cargo.toml; verified by hand against the LICENSE file at the root
    of their source repo (MPL-2.0 for the libcosmic-family crates, MIT for
    the window_clipboard-family ones) and recorded as clarifications in
    deny.toml.
